-- Haitian President in Stable Condition After Blood Clot on Lungs
-- B y   E r i c   S a b o
-- 2012-04-17T18:48:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/haitian-president-in-stable-condition-after-blood-clot-on-lungs.html
Haitian President Michel Martelly
is being treated in a Miami hospital for a blood clot in the
lungs.  Martelly, a former singer known as “Sweet Mickey,”
remains in stable condition after tests confirmed that he has a
pulmonary embolism, the president’s office  said  today on its
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Sabo in Panama City at 
 esabo1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 